## RSVP Link

To register for this event sign up here: [https://luma.com/eloljzc0](https://luma.com/eloljzc0).
No conference ticket required.

## About

This is a special one-off Zig Day event hosted at the MIT Museum in Boston!

TigerBeetle has kindly offered to sponsor a Zig Day that runs the day before
Systems Distributed 26, to give an opportunity to both locals and conference
attendees to experience a Zig Day.

**Zig Days are full-day collaborative programming events.**

We meet in the morning, introduce ourselves and form small groups to work
on learning / passion projects with the ultimate goal of learning systems
thinking and how to make software you can love.

[Here you can learn more about systems thinking and software you can love.](/about/)

The event is open to the public but spaces are limited; attendance is by
[registration](https://luma.com/eloljzc0) only.

The program will run as follows (times are approximate):

- 9:00 - 9:30: gathering and chit-chat
- 9:30 - 10:00: introductions, form groups, setup workstations
- 10:00 - 01:00: work on stuff together
- 01:00 - 02:30: lunch break
- 02:30 - 04:30: work on stuff together (continued)
- 04:30 - 05:00: show others what you built and what you learnt
